<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="153" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,849,1163]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,849,875]" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Members of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1897" box="[600,754,849,875]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Sparianthinae">Sparianthinae</taxonomicName>
are distinguished from those of the remaining 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bertkau" authorityYear="1872" box="[1304,1436,849,875]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sparassidae</taxonomicName>
subfamilies by the combination of the following characters: chelicerae with retromarginal teeth much smaller than promarginals (as large as in other subfamilies); trochanter with distal ventral margin smooth (notched in other subfamilies); metatarsal trilobate membrane with median lobe much smaller than lateral projections (as large as or larger in other subfamilies); and male palps with spoon-shaped median apophysis (absent in other subfamilies).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
